anagrelide	drug	acetylsalicylic acid	drug
false

It is known that CYPdgbAdgb is inhibited by several medicinal products , including DRUGA , and such medicinal products could theoretically adversely influence the clearance of DRUGB .
fluvoxamine	drug	anagrelide	drug
mechanism

DRUGA demonstrates some limited inhibitory activity towards CYPdgbAdgb which may present a theoretical potential for interaction with other coadministered medicinal products sharing that clearance mechanism e.g . DRUGB .

The concurrent use of two or more drugs with anticholinergic activity such as an DRUGN ( eg , DRUGA ) , an DRUGN ( eg , DRUGB ) , and / or a DRUGN ( eg , DRUGN ) commonly results in excessive anticholinergic effects , including dry mouth and associated dental complications , blurred vision , and , in patients exposed to high temperature and humidity , hyperpyrexia .

Hypotension : Patients on Diuretic Therapy : Patients on DRUGN and especially those in whom diuretic therapy was recently instituted , may occasionally experience an excessive reduction of blood pressure after initiation of therapy with DRUGA or DRUGB .
enalapril	drug	enalaprilat	drug
false

The possibility of hypotensive effects with DRUGA or DRUGB can be minimized by either discontinuing the DRUGN or increasing the salt intake prior to initiation of treatment with DRUGN or DRUGN .

No drugs are known to interfere with the conversion of DRUGA to DRUGB .
fosphenytoin	drug	phenytoin	drug
false

Conversion could be affected by alterations in the level of phosphatase activity , but given the abundance and wide distribution of phosphatases in the body it is unlikely that drugs would affect this activity enough to affect conversion of DRUGA to DRUGB .

DRUGA : Marked hypertension and tachycardia have been reported in association with concomitant administration of DRUGN and DRUGB .
Ketamine	drug	ketamine	drug
false

The administration of local DRUGN containing DRUGA or DRUGB to patients receiving DRUGN or DRUGN may produce severe , prolonged hypertension .
epinephrine	drug	norepinephrine	drug
false

Antagonism between DRUGA and DRUGB in vitro has been demonstrated .
lincomycin	drug	erythromycin	drug
effect

Commonly used drugs such as DRUGA and DRUGB have been specifically studied .
phenylpropanolamine	drug	pseudoephedrine	drug
false

Initial doses of DRUGN , such as DRUGA or DRUGB , should be reduced and titrated to achieve the desired response .
dopamine	drug	epinephrine	drug
false

DRUGN s : DRUGN increases the adrenergic effect of catecholamines such as DRUGA and DRUGB .
epinephrine	drug	norepinephrine	drug
false

Urinary acidifying agents These agents ( DRUGA , DRUGN , etc . ) increase the concentration of the ionized species of the DRUGB molecule , thereby increasing urinary excretion .
ammonium chloride	drug	amphetamine	drug
mechanism

DRUGN with DRUGA or DRUGB and possibly other DRUGN cause striking and sustained increases in the concentration of DRUGN in the brain ;
desipramine	drug	protriptyline	drug
false

DRUGN DRUGN , as well as a metabolite of DRUGA , slow DRUGB metabolism .

mechanism

DRUGA : DRUGN blocks dopamine and norepinephrine receptors , thus inhibiting the central stimulant effects of DRUGN and can be used to treat DRUGB poisoning .

false
